TargetName: The target point sources of each beam, when using the end point method.
Target: Default target-point information to use if the beam method is endpoint.
TargetTangentMethod: The method to use for the Target tangent.
TargetTangent: The tangent for the Target point for each beam.
TargetStrength: The strength of the tangent from the Target point for each beam.
LockRadius: Default target-point information to use if the beam method is endpoint.
bTargetAbsolute: Whether to treat the as an absolute position in world space.
bLockTarget: Whether to lock the Target to the life of the particle.
bLockTargetTangent: Whether to lock the Target to the life of the particle.
bLockTargetStength: Whether to lock the Target to the life of the particle.
